  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (04e6c91 2023-03-19T00:12:01.130238347Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen calling a contract that calls itself recursively an unbounded number of time, `forge` crashes with the following message:\r\n![core_dumped](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22668539/226211013-184c8ac1-7634-4509-80a9-50d148b750a9.png)\r\n\r\nThis bug happens when running `forge test` in the following repository: https://github.com/QGarchery/infinite-loop-oracle. I understand that the code is buggy because of the infinite recursion, but I assume that a different error message should be shown instead, such as a revert from the EVM.",
